#Celsius_to_Fahrenheit
#This script converts temperature between Fahrenheit to Celsius. To
#create a python converter for celsius and fahrenheit, you first have to 
#find out which formula to use. Fahrenheit to Celsius formula: (°F - 32)
#x 5/9 = °C or in plain english, First subtract 32, then multiply by 5, #then divide by 9.
#{0:0.1f}".format(celsius) is for Python3

cel = input("Please enter a temperature in Celsius:\n");
celsius = float(cel);
fahrenheit= (1.8*celsius) + 32;
print("{0:0.1f}".format(celsius),"Celsius =","{0:0.1f}".format(fahrenheit),"Fahrenheit" );

